{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WueW8fU1RR4uakHHUfCTeu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→use std::fs;\n     2→use std::path::Path;\n     3→\n     4→use toml_edit::{value, DocumentMut};\n     5→\n     6→use crate::shared::domain::WorkspaceConfig;\n     7→use crate::shared::error::AppResult;\n     8→\n     9→pub struct FileSystem;\n    10→\n    11→impl FileSystem {\n    12→    pub fn create_workspace(\n    13→        workspace_root: &Path,\n    14→        workspace_config: &str,\n    15→        required_directories: &[&str],\n    16→    ) -> AppResult<()> {\n    17→        fs::create_dir_all(workspace_root)?;\n    18→\n    19→        for directory in required_directories {\n    20→            fs::create_dir_all(workspace_root.join(directory))?;\n    21→        }\n    22→\n    23→        fs::write(workspace_root.join(\"workspace.toml\"), workspace_config)?;\n    24→        Ok(())\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    pub fn read_to_string(path: &Path) -> AppResult<String> {\n    28→        Ok(fs::read_to_string(path)?)\n    29→    }\n    30→\n    31→    pub fn render_workspace_config(config: &WorkspaceConfig) -> String {\n    32→        let mut document = DocumentMut::new();\n    33→        document[\"version\"] = value(i64::from(config.version));\n    34→        document[\"created_at\"] = value(config.created_at.to_rfc3339());\n    35→        document.to_string()\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46f86fe6-16b8-4d7e-86ab-a2a23388603c","uuid":"30b84a31-3928-4af4-bfc5-a3520330e20f","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs","content":"use std::fs;\nuse std::path::Path;\n\nuse toml_edit::{value, DocumentMut};\n\nuse crate::shared::domain::WorkspaceConfig;\nuse crate::shared::error::AppResult;\n\npub struct FileSystem;\n\nimpl FileSystem {\n    pub fn create_workspace(\n        workspace_root: &Path,\n        workspace_config: &str,\n        required_directories: &[&str],\n    ) -> AppResult<()> {\n        fs::create_dir_all(workspace_root)?;\n\n        for directory in required_directories {\n            fs::create_dir_all(workspace_root.join(directory))?;\n        }\n\n        fs::write(workspace_root.join(\"workspace.toml\"), workspace_config)?;\n        Ok(())\n    }\n\n    pub fn read_to_string(path: &Path) -> AppResult<String> {\n        Ok(fs::read_to_string(path)?)\n    }\n\n    pub fn render_workspace_config(config: &WorkspaceConfig) -> String {\n        let mut document = DocumentMut::new();\n        document[\"version\"] = value(i64::from(config.version));\n        document[\"created_at\"] = value(config.created_at.to_rfc3339());\n        document.to_string()\n    }\n}\n","numLines":38,"startLine":1,"totalLines":38}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0141sCgGZ3ErYfpq7PFWdeTz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of what's been completed and what needs to come next.\n\n**Completed:**\n- Loop 1: Foundation — Domain model, workspace init, flow discovery (roadmap slice 1)\n- Loop 2: Stage contract registry and deterministic artifact rendering (roadmap slice 2)\n\n**Roadmap slices remaining:**\n3. Workspace governance effective config + active project resolution\n4. Project/run canonical store + journal + query commands\n5. Agent execution facade with structured-output guarantee\n6. Standard preset vertical path (`run start`) end-to-end\n7. Retry/remediation, prompt review, resume, and failure class semantics\n\n\n8. Completion/acceptance/final-review behavior + amendment queue\n9. Docs and CI preset integration\n10. Requirements drafting and project-seed handoff\n11. Daemon routing, tasks, leases, watchers, rebase, interactive requirements path\n12. Cutover: conformance gate in CI\n\nLooking at the roadmap, slice 3 is relatively lean—just effective config resolution and active project tracking. Slice 4 is where the real substance lies, with the project and run canonical store plus journal and query commands that unlock the full run lifecycle. I should focus on that bigger piece next.\n\nActually, let me reconsider the dependencies here. Slice 3 and slice 4 are tightly intertwined—I need the effective config and active project resolution in place before building the store, but they're listed as separate slices for a reason. For slice 3, I'm looking at implementing config commands like show, get, set, and edit, plus active project tracking through a file in the workspace directory, effective config resolution that layers workspace defaults over project-level overrides, and the project select command that other commands will rely on. The roadmap distinguishes slice 3 as workspace governance and active project resolution, while slice 4 handles the project and run store itself.\n\nNow I need to think through what slice 3 actually requires structurally—the workspace config file needs to be richer than just version information, and I need to establish how the active project file gets created and managed.\n\nLooking at the spec more carefully, the config commands are straightforward: `config show` displays the effective configuration, `config get` retrieves a specific key, `config set` updates a value, and `config edit` opens the file in an editor. The workspace structure already defines `workspace.toml` and an `active-project` file, so I need to wire those together with the CLI commands and make sure the version check integrates properly.\n\nFor the actual config schema, I should keep it minimal and focused on what the master prompt requires: `prompt_review.enabled` to control whether prompt review is optional in the standard flow, backend and model defaults for later agent execution, and validation strictness settings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2145,"cache_read_input_tokens":39537,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2145},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46f86fe6-16b8-4d7e-86ab-a2a23388603c","uuid":"2d114319-01f0-4e6e-964d-f9d7a85edc4a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0141sCgGZ3ErYfpq7PFWdeTz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture of the project state. Let me analyze and produce the next feature spec.\n\n**Completed:**\n- Loop 1 (roadmap slice 1): Foundation — domain model, workspace init, flow discovery\n- Loop 2 (roadmap slice 2): Stage contract registry and deterministic artifact rendering\n\n**Next in roadmap:** Slice 3 — Workspace governance effective config + active project resolution\n\n# Feature: Workspace Governance Effective Config and Active Project Resolution\n\n## Description\nImplement roadmap slice 3: layered workspace configuration with `config show/get/set/edit` CLI commands, and active-project resolution via the `.ralph-burning/active-project` pointer file. The existing `workspace_governance` context currently handles workspace init and config loading but has no support for effective configuration (workspace-level defaults, runtime overrides), mutable config updates, or tracking which project is currently selected. This slice fills that gap so that downstream work (project/run canonical store in slice 4, agent execution in slice 5) can resolve effective settings and know which project commands target without explicit `--id` flags.\n\nThe config surface covers keys implied by the master prompt: `prompt_review.enabled` (controls whether the optional `prompt_review` stage runs in the `standard` flow), default backend family, default model overrides, and validation strictness. The implementation stores configuration in `workspace.toml` using a structured TOML schema, resolves effective values through a defaults-then-override chain, and enforces fail-fast on unsupported workspace versions (invariant already partially present, now wired through all config-reading paths).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `workspace.toml` schema is extended with an optional `[settings]` table supporting at minimum these keys: `prompt_review.enabled` (bool, default `true`), `default_flow` (string, must be a valid `FlowPreset`, default `\"standard\"`), `default_backend` (string, optional), `default_model` (string, optional). Unknown keys in `[settings]` are preserved on round-trip (forward-compatible editing).\n- [ ] An `EffectiveConfig` struct in `workspace_governance` resolves the full configuration by merging persisted `workspace.toml` settings with compiled defaults. Every supported key has a typed accessor with a documented default value. `EffectiveConfig::load(base_dir)` is the single entry point for all config reads.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config show` loads the workspace, checks the version (fail-fast on mismatch), and prints all effective settings as a human-readable TOML-like table showing each key, its effective value, and its source (`default` or `workspace.toml`).\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config get <key>` prints the effective value for a single key. Exits non-zero with a clear error for unknown keys.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config set <key> <value>` validates the key name and value type, writes the updated value into `workspace.toml` under `[settings]`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero for invalid keys or values (e.g., setting `default_flow` to an unknown preset).\n- [ ] `ralph-burning config edit` opens `workspace.toml` in `$EDITOR` (or `$VISUAL`, falling back to `vi`). After the editor exits, the file is re-validated; if validation fails, the user is warned on stderr and the command exits non-zero (but the file is not reverted — the user must fix manually).\n- [ ] `active-project` is a plain-text file in `.ralph-burning/` containing a single project ID (trimmed, no newline normalization issues). When absent, commands that require an active project fail with an explicit message naming `project select`.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project select <id>` validates that the project directory `.ralph-burning/projects/<id>/` exists and contains `project.toml`, writes the ID to `active-project`, and prints a confirmation. Exits non-zero if the project does not exist.\n- [ ] A `resolve_active_project(base_dir) -> AppResult<ProjectId>` function in `workspace_governance` reads and validates `active-project`, returning a typed `ProjectId` or a descriptive error. This function is the single resolution point for all commands that operate on the current project.\n- [ ] All config and active-project commands check workspace version first and fail fast on unsupported versions (wiring the existing `ensure_supported_workspace_version` through the CLI path).\n- [ ] The filesystem adapter (`adapters/fs.rs`) gains methods for atomic config writes (write-to-temp-then-rename) and active-project file read/write, keeping side effects behind the adapter boundary.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover: `EffectiveConfig` default resolution, override merging, round-trip serialization of extended `workspace.toml`, unknown-key preservation, invalid key/value rejection, active-project read/write/missing cases.\n- [ ] Integration tests cover: `config show` output format, `config get` known and unknown keys, `config set` valid and invalid mutations, `project select` with existing and non-existing project directories.\n- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature`: show effective config, get known key, get unknown key, set valid key, set invalid value, set invalid key, edit with valid result, edit with invalid result.\n- [ ] Gherkin scenarios added to `tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature`: select existing project, select non-existing project, resolve when no active project set, resolve after valid select.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass after all changes.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` — extend `WorkspaceConfig` with optional `settings: WorkspaceSettings` field; add `WorkspaceSettings` struct with typed config fields and defaults\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` — add error variants: `UnknownConfigKey`, `InvalidConfigValue`, `NoActiveProject`, `ProjectNotFound`, `EditorFailed`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs` — add `EffectiveConfig` struct with `load()`, `get()`, `set()` methods; add `resolve_active_project()` and `set_active_project()` functions; refactor config loading to use extended schema\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/config.rs` — (new) effective config resolution logic, key registry, default values, validation of key names and value types\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` — add `write_atomic()`, `read_active_project()`, `write_active_project()`, `open_editor()` methods\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/config.rs` — implement `show`, `get`, `set`, `edit` handlers replacing the current stubs\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` — implement `select` handler (other project subcommands remain stubs)\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/config_test.rs` — unit tests for effective config resolution, merging, serialization, key validation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/active_project_test.rs` — unit tests for active-project read/write/missing\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/workspace_config.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for config commands\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature` — Gherkin scenarios for active project resolution\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 (workspace init, `WorkspaceConfig`, filesystem adapter) and Loop 2 (flow preset validation for `default_flow` config key)\n- Blocks: Slice 4 (project/run canonical store needs `resolve_active_project` and effective config), Slice 5 (agent execution needs default backend/model config resolution), Slice 6 (`run start` needs active project and effective config for prompt_review gate)\n\n---"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2145,"cache_read_input_tokens":39537,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2145},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46f86fe6-16b8-4d7e-86ab-a2a23388603c","uuid":"e7668360-a3ce-4e21-bfb0-677932d075c1"}
